{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Jira Service Management Cloud*.
  {panel}

h3. Problem Definition
Fields are appearing in ticket details(in the portal/issue view - Jira Interface) and under the custom tab. 

h3. Steps to reproduce:
# Add a custom tab in the specific screen;
# Add fields to this custom tab;
# Add these fields to the request form;
# Create a ticket;
# Open this ticket under Jira UI;
# These fields will appear in both(ticket details and in the custom tab);
!Screen Shot 2020-11-10 at 17.30.37.png|thumbnail!

h3. Suggested Solution
It would be great if these fields were grouped only into the custom tab.

h3. Workaround 
None

Currently the 'Time To Resolution - elapsed/remaining' filters only works on tickets where the SLA is currently active. However for the completed tickets (the SLA in non-active) as well, we'd like to filter by specific (e.g. < 5h) time. 
{code}
"Time to resolution" = completed() AND "Time to resolution" < 5h
{code}
The only thing we can do right now is to filter issues based on whether the current SLA clock is running or not
{code}
"Time to resolution" = completed()
{code}

